faqs.answer:
think about a time when you needed something, and had no one to reach out to. think about having a group of people who were responsive to those needs. 

from that simple idea, this engine could be used to 
1) handle parts priorities in manufacturing; 
2) manage grocery stock based on community needs; 
3) enhance word-of-mouth business for solo repair people; 
or find a babysitter in the neighborhood.
